{"id":28423,"date":"2021-04-20T14:27:54","date_gmt":"2021-04-20T14:27:54","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/islamicscholarshipfund.org\/?page_id=28423"},"modified":"2023-12-20T17:18:41","modified_gmt":"2023-12-20T17:18:41","slug":"judicial-internship","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/islamicscholarshipfund.org\/judicial-internship\/","title":{"rendered":"Judicial Internship"},"content":{"rendered":"\n\n\t<h1><strong>Judicial <\/strong><strong>Internship Scholarship<br \/>\n<\/strong><\/h1>\n\t<p>The ISF Judicial Internship Scholarship application will open in February.<\/p>\n\t<h3>The ISF Judicial Internship Scholarship offers funding for law students who will intern with a\u00a0 state or federal judge. Eligible applicants who have been offered a judicial internship of at least 8-weeks can apply for this $2500 stipend.<\/h3>\n<h3>\n\t\tA Pipeline Program\n\t<\/h3>\n\t<p>The ISF Judicial Internship Scholarship is devoted to promoting and encouraging diversity and inclusion in the field of public interest law. Whether interning in Summer, Fall, or Spring semester, interns will gain real-world experience in the courtrooms and chambers of federal and state judges.<\/p>\n\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/islamicscholarshipfund.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/IMG_0118-e1614877205913.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_0118\" itemprop=\"image\" height=\"916\" width=\"2048\" title=\"IMG_0118\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\"  \/>\n\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/islamicscholarshipfund.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/Noorulain-Hasan.jpg\" alt=\"Noorulain Hasan\" itemprop=\"image\" height=\"801\" width=\"801\" title=\"Noorulain Hasan\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\"  \/>\n<h3>\n\t\tGoal\n\t<\/h3>\n<p>The ISF Judicial Internship Scholarship aims to expose American Muslim students to the privileges and responsibilities of working in a judge&#8217;s chambers. The program promotes and encourages diversity and inclusion in the public interest law field.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3>\n\t\tThe Process\n\t<\/h3>\n<p>Students that have received an offer for a judicial internship from a state or federal judge are eligible to apply. Students may count the program as an externship, in accordance with the rules of the students&#8217; respective law school.\u00a0 Students who receive the scholarship will receive a $2500 stipend.<\/p>\n\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/islamicscholarshipfund.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/Judge-Zia-Farqui-1.jpg\" alt=\"Judge Zia Farqui (1)\" itemprop=\"image\" height=\"1067\" width=\"1600\" title=\"Judge Zia Farqui (1)\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\"  \/>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\nThe ISF Judicial Internship promotes and encourages diversity and inclusion in the public interest law profession and judiciary.\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3>\n\t\tEligibility\n\t<\/h3>\n\t<ol>\n<li>Active member of the Muslim community<\/li>\n<li>Enrolled as a first-year or second-year law student at an accredited law school in the U.S.<\/li>\n<li>Received an offer for a judicial internship from a state or federal judge <strong>OR<\/strong> an ISF Law Scholarship recipient who is applying for a judicial internship through Just the Beginning<\/li>\n<li>A U.S. citizen, permanent resident of the United States or a DACA recipient.<\/li>\n<li>Preference may be given to those not receiving funding for the judicial internship from another source<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<h3>\n\t\tRequirements\n\t<\/h3>\n<ol>\n<li>60-second video introduction<\/li>\n<li>Resume<\/li>\n<li>Letter of recommendation<\/li>\n<li>450-word essay question<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<h3>\n\t\tInternship Benefits\n\t<\/h3>\n\t<ul>\n<li>Stipend of $2,500<\/li>\n<li>Professional leadership and law enrichment workshops throughout and after the program<\/li>\n<li>Networking opportunities<\/li>\n<li>Mentorship opportunities<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h2>\n\t\tProgram Timeline\n\t<\/h2>\n\t<ul>\n\t\t<li>\t\t\t\t\n\t\t<h4>Application<\/h4><p>ISF will start accepting online applications for the ISF Scholarship at the beginning of December of each year.<\/p><\/li><li>\t\t\t\t\n\t\t<h4>Deadline<\/h4><p>The deadline to apply for an ISF Scholarship (required for internship consideration) is late March or early April each year.<\/p><\/li><li>\t\t\t\t\n\t\t<h4>Application Review<\/h4><p>The Selection Committee will review applications from April-May<\/p><\/li><li>\t\t\t\t\n\t\t<h4>Scholarship Awarded<\/h4><p>Final decisions will be made in May and scholarships will be awarded shortly after.<\/p><\/li><li>\t\t\t\t\n\t\t<h4>Internship Begins<\/h4><p>Exact internship dates will be negotiated between candidates and the judge who will host them. Since the internship can happen in Spring, Summer, or Fall, the start date will likely be at the beginning of each of those respective semesters.<\/p><\/li><li>\t\t\t\t\n\t\t<h4>Sessions &#038; Workshops<\/h4><p>Interns are encouraged to attend ISF-hosted sessions and workshops throughout their internship period.<\/p><\/li><li>\t\t\t\t\n\t\t<h4>Exit Interview<\/h4><p>Interns will end the program with an exit interview. Upon completion, participants can join the ISF alumni network and continue to receive mentorship and support.<\/p><\/li>\t<\/ul>\n<h3>\n\t\tFAQS\n\t<\/h3>\n\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" id=\"fl-accordion--label-0\" tabindex=\"0\" aria-controls=\"fl-accordion--panel-0\">How many interns are selected?<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"#\" id=\"fl-accordion--icon-0\" tabindex=\"-1\" aria-controls=\"fl-accordion--panel-0\"><i>Expand<\/i><\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>The amount of recipients depends on the amount of funding available. ISF generally awards 4-6 interns each year.<\/p>\n\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" id=\"fl-accordion--label-1\" tabindex=\"0\" aria-controls=\"fl-accordion--panel-1\">Does the internship provide payment?<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"#\" id=\"fl-accordion--icon-1\" tabindex=\"-1\" aria-controls=\"fl-accordion--panel-1\"><i>Expand<\/i><\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>Yes. Interns will receive $2,500 during the 8-week period.<\/p>\n\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" id=\"fl-accordion--label-2\" tabindex=\"0\" aria-controls=\"fl-accordion--panel-2\">Can I work a part time job during the internship?<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"#\" id=\"fl-accordion--icon-2\" tabindex=\"-1\" aria-controls=\"fl-accordion--panel-2\"><i>Expand<\/i><\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>It is highly discouraged to take on part-time work during your internship, as you will have numerous demands and responsibilities that come along with your role<\/p>\n\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Judicial Internship Scholarship The ISF Judicial Internship Scholarship application will open in February. The ISF Judicial Internship Scholarship offers funding for law students who will intern with a\u00a0 state or federal judge. Eligible applicants who have been offered a judicial internship of at least 8-weeks can apply for this $2500 stipend. A Pipeline Program The&hellip;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":4,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":{"footnotes":""},"yoast_head":"<!-- This site is optimized with the Yoast SEO plugin v21.7 - https:\/\/yoast.com\/wordpress\/plugins\/seo\/ -->\n<title>Judicial Internship - Islamic Scholarship Fund<\/title>\n<meta name=\"robots\" content=\"index, follow, max-snippet:-1, max-image-preview:large, max-video-preview:-1\" \/>\n<link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"https:\/\/islamicscholarshipfund.org\/judicial-internship\/\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:locale\" content=\"en_US\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:type\" content=\"article\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:title\" content=\"Judicial Internship - Islamic Scholarship Fund\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:description\" content=\"Judicial Internship Scholarship The ISF Judicial Internship Scholarship application will open in February. The ISF Judicial Internship Scholarship offers funding fo